      "excerpt": "From clear mountain views to vibrant festivals, learn when to plan your Nepal adventure for the best experience.",
      "content": "<h2>At&nbsp;a&nbsp;Glance:&nbsp;Nepal&nbsp;Travel&nbsp;Seasons</h2><p>If&nbsp;you’re&nbsp;looking&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;quick&nbsp;answer,&nbsp;here&nbsp;is&nbsp;how&nbsp;we&nbsp;categorize&nbsp;the&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;and&nbsp;touring&nbsp;calendar:</p><table style=\"border: 1px solid #000;\"><tbody><tr><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Season</strong></td><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Months</strong></td><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Best&nbsp;For</strong></td><td data-row=\"1\"><strong>Visibility&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Weather</strong></td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"2\"><strong>Peak&nbsp;(Spring)</strong></td><td data-row=\"2\">March&nbsp;–&nbsp;May</td><td data-row=\"2\">Everest/Annapurna&nbsp;Trekking</td><td data-row=\"2\">Crystal&nbsp;clear,&nbsp;Rhododendrons&nbsp;in&nbsp;bloom</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"3\"><strong>Low&nbsp;(Monsoon)</strong></td><td data-row=\"3\">June&nbsp;–&nbsp;August</td><td data-row=\"3\">Mustang/Dolpo&nbsp;(Rain&nbsp;Shadow)</td><td data-row=\"3\">Lush&nbsp;greenery,&nbsp;fewer&nbsp;tourists,&nbsp;rain</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"4\"><strong>Peak&nbsp;(Autumn)</strong></td><td data-row=\"4\">Sept&nbsp;–&nbsp;Nov</td><td data-row=\"4\">Peak&nbsp;Climbing&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Festivals</td><td data-row=\"4\">Best&nbsp;visibility,&nbsp;crisp&nbsp;air,&nbsp;Dashain/Tihar</td></tr><tr><td data-row=\"5\"><strong>Off-Peak&nbsp;(Winter)</strong></td><td data-row=\"5\">Dec&nbsp;–&nbsp;Feb</td><td data-row=\"5\">Jungle&nbsp;Safaris&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Lowland&nbsp;Tours</td><td data-row=\"5\">Sunny&nbsp;days,&nbsp;cold&nbsp;nights,&nbsp;quiet&nbsp;trails</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>1.&nbsp;Spring&nbsp;(March&nbsp;to&nbsp;May):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Season&nbsp;of&nbsp;Flowers</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;High-altitude&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;and&nbsp;wildlife&nbsp;spotting.</p><p>We&nbsp;consider&nbsp;Spring&nbsp;the&nbsp;second-best&nbsp;time&nbsp;for&nbsp;trekking,&nbsp;but&nbsp;the&nbsp;absolute&nbsp;best&nbsp;for&nbsp;nature&nbsp;lovers.&nbsp;As&nbsp;the&nbsp;snow&nbsp;melts,&nbsp;the&nbsp;trails&nbsp;to&nbsp;<strong>Annapurna</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Everest</strong>&nbsp;become&nbsp;vibrant&nbsp;with&nbsp;red&nbsp;and&nbsp;pink&nbsp;rhododendrons.</p><ul><li><strong>Why&nbsp;we&nbsp;love&nbsp;it:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;temperatures&nbsp;are&nbsp;moderate,&nbsp;making&nbsp;long&nbsp;trekking&nbsp;days&nbsp;comfortable.</li><li><strong>Pro&nbsp;Tip:</strong>&nbsp;If&nbsp;you’re&nbsp;visiting&nbsp;<strong>Chitwan&nbsp;National&nbsp;Park</strong>,&nbsp;this&nbsp;is&nbsp;when&nbsp;the&nbsp;tall&nbsp;grass&nbsp;is&nbsp;cut,&nbsp;making&nbsp;it&nbsp;much&nbsp;easier&nbsp;to&nbsp;spot&nbsp;tigers&nbsp;and&nbsp;rhinos.</li></ul><h2>2.&nbsp;Autumn&nbsp;(September&nbsp;to&nbsp;November):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Gold&nbsp;Standard</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;Clear&nbsp;mountain&nbsp;views&nbsp;and&nbsp;cultural&nbsp;immersion.</p><p>This&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;most&nbsp;popular&nbsp;time&nbsp;to&nbsp;visit&nbsp;Nepal.&nbsp;After&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon&nbsp;rains&nbsp;wash&nbsp;away&nbsp;the&nbsp;dust,&nbsp;the&nbsp;atmosphere&nbsp;is&nbsp;at&nbsp;its&nbsp;clearest.</p><ul><li><strong>The&nbsp;View:</strong>&nbsp;You&nbsp;get&nbsp;those&nbsp;&quot;postcard-perfect&quot;&nbsp;views&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Himalayas&nbsp;from&nbsp;everywhere—Nagarkot,&nbsp;Sarangkot,&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;high&nbsp;passes.</li><li><strong>Festivals:</strong>&nbsp;We&nbsp;highly&nbsp;recommend&nbsp;visiting&nbsp;during&nbsp;<strong>Dashain&nbsp;and&nbsp;Tihar</strong>&nbsp;(October/November).&nbsp;The&nbsp;energy&nbsp;in&nbsp;Kathmandu&nbsp;is&nbsp;electric,&nbsp;and&nbsp;you’ll&nbsp;experience&nbsp;the&nbsp;true&nbsp;heart&nbsp;of&nbsp;Nepali&nbsp;hospitality.</li></ul><h2>3.&nbsp;Winter&nbsp;(December&nbsp;to&nbsp;February):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Peaceful&nbsp;Choice</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;Photography&nbsp;and&nbsp;budget-friendly&nbsp;cultural&nbsp;tours.</p><p>While&nbsp;the&nbsp;high-altitude&nbsp;passes&nbsp;may&nbsp;be&nbsp;blocked&nbsp;by&nbsp;snow,&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Kathmandu&nbsp;Valley</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Lumbini</strong>,&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Pokhara</strong>&nbsp;remain&nbsp;pleasantly&nbsp;sunny&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;day.</p><ul><li><strong>The&nbsp;Perk:</strong>&nbsp;Trails&nbsp;are&nbsp;empty.&nbsp;If&nbsp;you&nbsp;don’t&nbsp;mind&nbsp;the&nbsp;cold&nbsp;(night&nbsp;temps&nbsp;can&nbsp;drop&nbsp;below&nbsp;freezing),&nbsp;you’ll&nbsp;have&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains&nbsp;all&nbsp;to&nbsp;yourself.</li><li><strong>Zeo’s&nbsp;Pick:</strong>&nbsp;Try&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>Ghorepani&nbsp;Poon&nbsp;Hill</strong>&nbsp;trek&nbsp;in&nbsp;winter&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;stunning&nbsp;sunrise&nbsp;without&nbsp;the&nbsp;crowds.</li></ul><h2>4.&nbsp;Summer/Monsoon&nbsp;(June&nbsp;to&nbsp;August):&nbsp;The&nbsp;Off-Beat&nbsp;Adventure</h2><p><strong>Best&nbsp;for:</strong>&nbsp;Trans-Himalayan&nbsp;treks&nbsp;and&nbsp;lush&nbsp;landscapes.</p><p>Most&nbsp;people&nbsp;avoid&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon,&nbsp;but&nbsp;we&nbsp;believe&nbsp;it’s&nbsp;Nepal’s&nbsp;best-kept&nbsp;secret&nbsp;for&nbsp;specific&nbsp;regions.</p><ul><li><strong>Rain&nbsp;Shadow&nbsp;Areas:</strong>&nbsp;Places&nbsp;like&nbsp;<strong>Upper&nbsp;Mustang</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Upper&nbsp;Dolpo</strong>&nbsp;sit&nbsp;behind&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains,&nbsp;meaning&nbsp;they&nbsp;stay&nbsp;dry&nbsp;while&nbsp;the&nbsp;rest&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;country&nbsp;is&nbsp;rainy.</li><li><strong>Lush&nbsp;Scenery:</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;hills&nbsp;turn&nbsp;an&nbsp;incredible&nbsp;shade&nbsp;of&nbsp;emerald&nbsp;green,&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;waterfalls&nbsp;are&nbsp;at&nbsp;their&nbsp;most&nbsp;powerful.</li></ul><h2>Frequently&nbsp;Asked&nbsp;Questions&nbsp;(ZEO&nbsp;Focus)</h2><h3><strong>What&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;cheapest&nbsp;month&nbsp;to&nbsp;fly&nbsp;to&nbsp;Nepal?</strong></h3><p>Typically,&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon&nbsp;months&nbsp;(<strong>June&nbsp;to&nbsp;August</strong>)&nbsp;and&nbsp;late&nbsp;winter&nbsp;(<strong>January</strong>)&nbsp;offer&nbsp;the&nbsp;lowest&nbsp;airfares&nbsp;and&nbsp;hotel&nbsp;rates.&nbsp;We&nbsp;can&nbsp;help&nbsp;you&nbsp;find&nbsp;&quot;off-season&quot;&nbsp;luxury&nbsp;stays&nbsp;at&nbsp;a&nbsp;fraction&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;price.</p><h3><strong>When&nbsp;is&nbsp;the&nbsp;best&nbsp;time&nbsp;for&nbsp;an&nbsp;Everest&nbsp;Base&nbsp;Camp&nbsp;trek?</strong></h3><p>The&nbsp;&quot;window&quot;&nbsp;is&nbsp;usually&nbsp;<strong>late&nbsp;April&nbsp;to&nbsp;mid-May</strong>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<strong>October&nbsp;to&nbsp;November</strong>.&nbsp;These&nbsp;months&nbsp;offer&nbsp;the&nbsp;safest&nbsp;conditions&nbsp;and&nbsp;best&nbsp;visibility&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;world’s&nbsp;highest&nbsp;peak.</p><h3><strong>Is&nbsp;Nepal&nbsp;safe&nbsp;to&nbsp;visit&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;monsoon?</strong></h3><p>Yes,&nbsp;but&nbsp;travel&nbsp;requires&nbsp;flexibility.&nbsp;While&nbsp;flights&nbsp;to&nbsp;Lukla&nbsp;may&nbsp;be&nbsp;delayed&nbsp;due&nbsp;to&nbsp;clouds,&nbsp;road&nbsp;trips&nbsp;through&nbsp;the&nbsp;valley&nbsp;and&nbsp;cultural&nbsp;tours&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;cities&nbsp;are&nbsp;perfectly&nbsp;fine.</p><h2>Start&nbsp;Your&nbsp;Journey&nbsp;with&nbsp;Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</h2><p>Choosing&nbsp;the&nbsp;right&nbsp;season&nbsp;depends&nbsp;on&nbsp;what&nbsp;you&nbsp;want&nbsp;to&nbsp;experience.&nbsp;Whether&nbsp;it&#39;s&nbsp;a&nbsp;high-altitude&nbsp;adrenaline&nbsp;rush&nbsp;or&nbsp;a&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;journey&nbsp;through&nbsp;ancient&nbsp;temples,&nbsp;we&nbsp;handle&nbsp;the&nbsp;logistics&nbsp;so&nbsp;you&nbsp;can&nbsp;focus&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;views.</p>",
