      "title": "Altitude Sickness: Prevention and Management",
      "excerpt": "Expert advice on recognizing, preventing, and dealing with altitude sickness during high-altitude treks.",
      "content": "<h1>Altitude&nbsp;Sickness:&nbsp;The&nbsp;Ultimate&nbsp;Prevention&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Management&nbsp;Guide</h1><p>Scaling&nbsp;the&nbsp;Himalayas&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;dream&nbsp;for&nbsp;many,&nbsp;but&nbsp;the&nbsp;&quot;thin&nbsp;air&quot;&nbsp;above&nbsp;3,000&nbsp;meters&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;formidable&nbsp;challenge.&nbsp;At&nbsp;<strong>Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</strong>,&nbsp;your&nbsp;safety&nbsp;is&nbsp;our&nbsp;baseline.&nbsp;Understanding&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Sickness—or&nbsp;Acute&nbsp;Mountain&nbsp;Sickness&nbsp;(AMS)—is&nbsp;the&nbsp;difference&nbsp;between&nbsp;reaching&nbsp;the&nbsp;summit&nbsp;and&nbsp;a&nbsp;forced&nbsp;helicopter&nbsp;evacuation.</p><p>Here&nbsp;is&nbsp;our&nbsp;expert&nbsp;manual&nbsp;on&nbsp;how&nbsp;we&nbsp;help&nbsp;you&nbsp;prevent,&nbsp;identify,&nbsp;and&nbsp;manage&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;sickness&nbsp;during&nbsp;your&nbsp;Nepal&nbsp;trek.</p><h2>1.&nbsp;Understanding&nbsp;the&nbsp;Spectrum&nbsp;of&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Illness</h2><p>Altitude&nbsp;sickness&nbsp;isn&#39;t&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;condition;&nbsp;it&nbsp;exists&nbsp;on&nbsp;a&nbsp;spectrum.&nbsp;We&nbsp;train&nbsp;our&nbsp;guides&nbsp;to&nbsp;monitor&nbsp;for&nbsp;three&nbsp;specific&nbsp;types:</p><ul><li><strong>AMS&nbsp;(Acute&nbsp;Mountain&nbsp;Sickness):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;most&nbsp;common&nbsp;form.&nbsp;It&nbsp;feels&nbsp;like&nbsp;a&nbsp;bad&nbsp;hangover&nbsp;(headache,&nbsp;nausea,&nbsp;fatigue).</li><li><strong>HAPE&nbsp;(High&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Pulmonary&nbsp;Edema):</strong>&nbsp;Fluid&nbsp;buildup&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;lungs.&nbsp;Signs&nbsp;include&nbsp;a&nbsp;persistent&nbsp;cough&nbsp;and&nbsp;extreme&nbsp;breathlessness&nbsp;even&nbsp;while&nbsp;resting.</li><li><strong>HACE&nbsp;(High&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Cerebral&nbsp;Edema):</strong>&nbsp;Fluid&nbsp;buildup&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;brain.&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;medical&nbsp;emergency&nbsp;marked&nbsp;by&nbsp;confusion&nbsp;and&nbsp;a&nbsp;&quot;drunken&nbsp;gait&quot;&nbsp;(ataxia).</li></ul><h2>2.&nbsp;Our&nbsp;&quot;Golden&nbsp;Rules&quot;&nbsp;for&nbsp;Prevention</h2><p>We&nbsp;don&#39;t&nbsp;leave&nbsp;acclimatization&nbsp;to&nbsp;chance.&nbsp;We&nbsp;build&nbsp;every&nbsp;itinerary&nbsp;around&nbsp;these&nbsp;non-negotiable&nbsp;rules:</p><h3><strong>The&nbsp;500m&nbsp;Rule</strong></h3><p>Once&nbsp;we&nbsp;pass&nbsp;3,000m&nbsp;(9,842ft),&nbsp;we&nbsp;ensure&nbsp;your&nbsp;sleeping&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;does&nbsp;not&nbsp;increase&nbsp;by&nbsp;more&nbsp;than&nbsp;<strong>300–500&nbsp;meters&nbsp;per&nbsp;day</strong>.&nbsp;Every&nbsp;1,000m&nbsp;of&nbsp;gain,&nbsp;we&nbsp;schedule&nbsp;a&nbsp;mandatory&nbsp;acclimatization&nbsp;day.</p><h3><strong>Climb&nbsp;High,&nbsp;Sleep&nbsp;Low</strong></h3><p>This&nbsp;is&nbsp;our&nbsp;favorite&nbsp;strategy.&nbsp;During&nbsp;&quot;rest&nbsp;days&quot;&nbsp;in&nbsp;Namche&nbsp;Bazaar&nbsp;or&nbsp;Manang,&nbsp;we&nbsp;take&nbsp;you&nbsp;on&nbsp;a&nbsp;short&nbsp;hike&nbsp;to&nbsp;a&nbsp;higher&nbsp;ridge&nbsp;(e.g.,&nbsp;Everest&nbsp;View&nbsp;Hotel)&nbsp;before&nbsp;returning&nbsp;to&nbsp;a&nbsp;lower&nbsp;elevation&nbsp;to&nbsp;sleep.&nbsp;This&nbsp;triggers&nbsp;your&nbsp;body&nbsp;to&nbsp;produce&nbsp;more&nbsp;red&nbsp;blood&nbsp;cells&nbsp;while&nbsp;you&nbsp;rest.</p><h3><strong>Hydration&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Nutrition</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>The&nbsp;4-Liter&nbsp;Goal:</strong>&nbsp;We&nbsp;encourage&nbsp;drinking&nbsp;3–4&nbsp;liters&nbsp;of&nbsp;water&nbsp;daily.&nbsp;Dehydration&nbsp;mimics&nbsp;and&nbsp;worsens&nbsp;AMS.</li><li><strong>Garlic&nbsp;Soup:</strong>&nbsp;A&nbsp;local&nbsp;Himalayan&nbsp;secret&nbsp;we&nbsp;swear&nbsp;by!&nbsp;Garlic&nbsp;is&nbsp;believed&nbsp;to&nbsp;help&nbsp;thin&nbsp;the&nbsp;blood&nbsp;and&nbsp;aid&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;circulation.</li><li><strong>The&nbsp;&quot;No-Go&quot;&nbsp;List:</strong>&nbsp;No&nbsp;alcohol,&nbsp;no&nbsp;smoking,&nbsp;and&nbsp;no&nbsp;sleeping&nbsp;pills.&nbsp;These&nbsp;suppress&nbsp;your&nbsp;breathing&nbsp;rate—the&nbsp;last&nbsp;thing&nbsp;you&nbsp;want&nbsp;at&nbsp;5,000&nbsp;meters.</li></ul><h2>3.&nbsp;Management:&nbsp;What&nbsp;Happens&nbsp;if&nbsp;You&nbsp;Get&nbsp;Sick?</h2><p>At&nbsp;<strong>Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</strong>,&nbsp;our&nbsp;motto&nbsp;is:&nbsp;<em>&quot;Don&#39;t&nbsp;go&nbsp;up&nbsp;until&nbsp;symptoms&nbsp;go&nbsp;down.&quot;</em></p><ol><li><strong>Stop&nbsp;Immediately:</strong>&nbsp;If&nbsp;you&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;headache&nbsp;and&nbsp;nausea,&nbsp;we&nbsp;halt&nbsp;the&nbsp;ascent.&nbsp;You&nbsp;stay&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;current&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;for&nbsp;24–48&nbsp;hours.</li><li><strong>Medication&nbsp;(Diamox):</strong>&nbsp;Many&nbsp;of&nbsp;our&nbsp;trekkers&nbsp;use&nbsp;<strong>Acetazolamide&nbsp;(Diamox)</strong>&nbsp;as&nbsp;a&nbsp;preventative.&nbsp;It&nbsp;helps&nbsp;you&nbsp;breathe&nbsp;deeper&nbsp;and&nbsp;faster.&nbsp;<em>Always&nbsp;consult&nbsp;your&nbsp;doctor&nbsp;before&nbsp;your&nbsp;trip.</em></li><li><strong>The&nbsp;Immediate&nbsp;Descent:</strong>&nbsp;If&nbsp;symptoms&nbsp;worsen&nbsp;or&nbsp;signs&nbsp;of&nbsp;HAPE/HACE&nbsp;appear,&nbsp;we&nbsp;begin&nbsp;an&nbsp;immediate&nbsp;descent&nbsp;of&nbsp;at&nbsp;least&nbsp;500–1,000m.</li><li><strong>Oxygen&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Gamow&nbsp;Bags:</strong>&nbsp;On&nbsp;high-pass&nbsp;treks,&nbsp;we&nbsp;carry&nbsp;supplemental&nbsp;oxygen&nbsp;and&nbsp;portable&nbsp;hyperbaric&nbsp;chambers&nbsp;(Gamow&nbsp;bags)&nbsp;to&nbsp;stabilize&nbsp;guests&nbsp;before&nbsp;evacuation.</li></ol><h2>ZEO&nbsp;FAQ:&nbsp;Altitude&nbsp;Sickness&nbsp;in&nbsp;Nepal</h2><h3><strong>Can&nbsp;fitness&nbsp;prevent&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;sickness?</strong></h3><p>No.&nbsp;Interestingly,&nbsp;being&nbsp;&quot;too&nbsp;fit&quot;&nbsp;can&nbsp;sometimes&nbsp;be&nbsp;a&nbsp;risk&nbsp;factor&nbsp;because&nbsp;athletes&nbsp;tend&nbsp;to&nbsp;hike&nbsp;faster&nbsp;than&nbsp;their&nbsp;bodies&nbsp;can&nbsp;acclimatize.&nbsp;AMS&nbsp;doesn&#39;t&nbsp;care&nbsp;about&nbsp;your&nbsp;marathon&nbsp;time—it&nbsp;only&nbsp;cares&nbsp;about&nbsp;your&nbsp;pace&nbsp;of&nbsp;ascent.</p><h3><strong>What&nbsp;does&nbsp;an&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;headache&nbsp;feel&nbsp;like?</strong></h3><p>It&nbsp;is&nbsp;usually&nbsp;a&nbsp;throbbing&nbsp;pain,&nbsp;often&nbsp;felt&nbsp;behind&nbsp;the&nbsp;eyes&nbsp;or&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;temples,&nbsp;that&nbsp;gets&nbsp;worse&nbsp;when&nbsp;bending&nbsp;over&nbsp;or&nbsp;lying&nbsp;down.</p><h3><strong>Does&nbsp;travel&nbsp;insurance&nbsp;cover&nbsp;altitude&nbsp;sickness?</strong></h3><p>Most&nbsp;standard&nbsp;plans&nbsp;do&nbsp;not.&nbsp;We&nbsp;require&nbsp;all&nbsp;our&nbsp;guests&nbsp;to&nbsp;have&nbsp;specific&nbsp;<strong>High-Altitude&nbsp;Trekking&nbsp;Insurance</strong>&nbsp;that&nbsp;covers&nbsp;helicopter&nbsp;evacuation&nbsp;up&nbsp;to&nbsp;6,000m.</p><h2>Trek&nbsp;Safely&nbsp;with&nbsp;Zeo&nbsp;Tourism</h2><p>We&nbsp;believe&nbsp;the&nbsp;mountains&nbsp;should&nbsp;be&nbsp;enjoyed,&nbsp;not&nbsp;&quot;conquered&quot;&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;expense&nbsp;of&nbsp;your&nbsp;health.&nbsp;Our&nbsp;itineraries&nbsp;are&nbsp;designed&nbsp;by&nbsp;experts&nbsp;who&nbsp;live&nbsp;and&nbsp;breathe&nbsp;the&nbsp;Himalayas.</p>",
